         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility"> ¶ It is understood that Mr Fergusson the Inspector of State Forests submitted to the late Government an Estimate of the cost of properly administering the department of the Botanic Gardens ¶ In the e...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">M70.04.27<seg rend="FootnoteReference"
                    style="text-transform: none; font-variant: normal; font-size: 9pt; "/>
            </p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">William Odgers to John MacPherson</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">V70/8814, unit 468, VPRS 3991 inward registered correspondence, VA 475 Chief Secretary's Department, Public Record Office, Victoria.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                  <p rend="FootnoteText"
                     style="margin-left: 0.1666in; text-indent: -0.1666in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-weight: bold; ">To proof.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>It is understood that Mr Fergusson the Inspector of State Forests submitted to the late Government an Estimate of the cost of properly administering the department of the Botanic Gardens<seg rend="FootnoteReference"
                    style="text-transform: none; font-variant: normal; font-size: 9pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.1666in; text-indent: -0.1666in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #0070C0; ">In the estimates of expenditure the</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #0070C0; ">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Botanic Gardens were</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #0070C0; ">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>routinely<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #0070C0; ">treated as part of the Department of the Government Botanist, and were not funded as a specific item.</seg>
                     </p>
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; margin-left: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-weight: bold; color: #C00000; ">If that is how the budget line as interpreted it was convenient, as the Gov botanist narrow sense was an added extra!</seg>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>— The Chief Secretary desires me to say he would be obliged to the Hon: the Commissioner of Crown Lands and Survey will send it to him for perusal tomorrow morning<seg rend="FootnoteReference"
                    style="text-transform: none; font-variant: normal; font-size: 9pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn2" n="3">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.1666in; text-indent: -0.1666in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The Assistant Commissioner of Crown Lands and Survey, C. Hodgkinson replied on 28 April: 'The Estimate alluded to was not received in the Land's Office Registry, and was consequently not recorded. It was probably retained by the Honble J. M'Kean as a document unconnected with the ordinary business of the Lands Dept'.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
         </div>
      </body>
   </text>
